description:
You are a chemical process engineer. Research thermophysical properties for Methanol, Toluene, and 1,1,1,2-Tetrafluoroethane (R-134a) using the NIST Chemistry WebBook (https://webbook.nist.gov/chemistry/). For each fluid, identify the CAS Registry Number, Molecular Weight (g/mol), Critical Temperature (Tc) in Kelvin, and Critical Pressure (Pc) in bar (converting from other units if necessary). Create a Firefox bookmark folder named 'Process Design Data' containing the specific NIST properties page for each fluid. Save the collected data to ~/Documents/fluid_properties.json using the following structure:
{
  "methanol": { "cas_registry_number": "...", "molecular_weight_g_mol": 0.0, "critical_temperature_k": 0.0, "critical_pressure_bar": 0.0 },
  "toluene": { "cas_registry_number": "...", "molecular_weight_g_mol": 0.0, "critical_temperature_k": 0.0, "critical_pressure_bar": 0.0 },
  "r134a": { "cas_registry_number": "...", "molecular_weight_g_mol": 0.0, "critical_temperature_k": 0.0, "critical_pressure_bar": 0.0 }
}
